form.text:
Lower yourself until you’re
on the level of your cat’s eyes. Kitties get scared if you suddenly stick out your hand while standing.
If kitty approaches and rubs against you, that means they've accepted you as their servant. Now you can pet its chin, nape of the neck, and flanks!

It’s scary to get too close or shout loudly.
Keep your distance
and approach slowly.

Staring into kitty's eyes
means you want to fight... Slowly blink your eyes. Cats will respond if they like you.
